'''ClockworkMod''' is a software company, owned by Koushik "Koush" Dutta,<ref>{{cite web|title=Koushik Dutta|website=LinkedIn|url=https://www.linkedin.com/pub/koushik-dutta/5/517/3a5|accessdate=26 August 2015}}</ref> which develops various software products for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] smartphones and tablets. The company is primarily known for its custom [[Recovery_(Android_OS)|recovery]] image, known as ClockworkMod Recovery, which is used in many custom made ROMs.

== ClockworkMod Recovery ==
ClockworkMod Recovery is an Android custom recovery image. Once installed, this recovery image replaces your Android device's stock recovery image. Using this recovery image, various system-level operations can be performed. For example, one can create and restore partition backups, [[Rooting (Android OS)|root]], install / repair / upgrade system software and/or [[List of custom Android firmware|custom ROM]]s, and use other developer tools.

ClockworkMod Recovery is free and open-source software, released under the terms of the Apache License 2.0 software license.<ref>Based on: {{cite web|title=android_bootable_recovery/NOTICE at cm-12.0 · CyanogenMod/android_bootable_recovery|url=https://github.com/CyanogenMod/android_bootable_recovery/blob/cm-12.0/NOTICE|publisher=GitHub, Inc|accessdate=26 August 2015}}</ref> The ClockworkMod Recovery source code is included in the [[CyanogenMod]] source code tree.<ref>{{cite web|title=clockworkmod source code - Google Search|url=http://www.google.com/search?q=clockworkmod+source+code|accessdate=26 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Porting ClockworkMod Recovery to a New Device|url=http://xda-university.com/as-a-developer/porting-clockworkmod-recovery-to-a-new-device|website=XDA-University|accessdate=26 August 2015}}</ref>

