{{SHORTDESC:civil engineer}} '''Elizabeth Bragg''' (1854 - 1929) was the first woman to receive a civil engineering degree from an American university.
== Biography == Elizabeth Bragg receiving her degree in [[civil engineering]] from the [[University of California, Berkeley|University of California at Berkley]] in 1876.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Writers |first1=Staff |title=10 Female Engineers Who Helped Pave the Way - BachelorsDegreeOnline.com |url=https://www.bachelorsdegreeonline.com/blog/2012/10-female-engineers-who-helped-pave-the-way/ |website=BachelorsDegreeOnline.com |accessdate=28 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=History of Women Engineers |url=https://alltogether.swe.org/2018/03/women-in-engineering-history/ |website=All Together |accessdate=28 August 2018 |date=7 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Rankin-Perez |first1=Julie |title=What’s it like to be a woman working in the energy industry? |url=https://www.theguardian.com/big-energy-debate/2014/dec/23/woman-in-energy-industry |website=the Guardian |accessdate=28 August 2018 |language=en |date=23 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=LeBold; LeBold|first=William K; Dona J|date=March 1998|title=Women engineers: A historical perspective|url=https://search.proquest.com/materialscienceengineering/docview/236163808/citation/5F1E14614DB8488DPQ/1?accountid=14667|journal=ASEE Prism|volume=7|pages=|via=}}</ref> Bragg married George Cumming in 1888, a civil engineer with the [[Southern Pacific Transportation Company|Southern Pacific Railroad Company]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://csengineermag.com/article/the-first-lady-of-structural-engineering/|title=The first lady of structural engineering - Civil + Structural Engineer magazine|work=Civil + Structural Engineer magazine|access-date=2018-09-18|language=en-US}}</ref> Elizabeth Bragg Cumming died on the 10 November 1929, and is buried in California.<ref>{{cite web |title=Elizabeth Bragg Cumming (1858-1929) - Find A... |url=https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/69474165 |website=www.findagrave.com |accessdate=28 August 2018}}</ref> == References == {{reflist}}
